
# Project 09 — News Category Classification (NLP)

This project implements a multi-class text classification system that automatically categorizes news articles into predefined categories using Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Machine Learning.

The system uses TF-IDF vectorization and Logistic Regression to classify news into four major categories: Business, Technology, Sports, and Health.

---

## 📌 Project Objectives

The main goals of this project are to:

- Preprocess and clean news text data
- Convert text into numerical features using TF-IDF
- Train a multi-class classification model
- Perform train/validation split
- Evaluate performance using Macro F1-score
- Analyze errors using a confusion matrix
- Visualize misclassifications
- Save trained models and metrics
- Provide reusable prediction capability

