## 🧠 Methodology

### 1. Text Vectorization (TF-IDF)

TF-IDF (Term Frequency–Inverse Document Frequency) converts raw text into numerical features based on word importance.

* Removes common stop words
* Highlights meaningful terms
* Reduces noise

This improves classification performance.

---

### 2. Classification Model (Logistic Regression)

A multi-class Logistic Regression model is used because:

* It performs well for text classification
* It is fast and scalable
* It produces interpretable results

The model automatically handles multiple categories.

---

### 3. Train / Validation Split

The dataset is split into:

* 75% Training Data
* 25% Validation Data

Stratified sampling ensures equal category distribution in both sets.

This prevents biased evaluation.

---

### 4. Model Evaluation

Performance is measured using:

* Macro F1-score

Macro F1 treats all categories equally and balances precision and recall.

This is suitable for multi-class classification.

---

### 5. Error Analysis (Confusion Matrix)

A confusion matrix is generated to analyze classification errors.

It shows:

* Correct predictions (diagonal)
* Misclassifications (off-diagonal)

This helps identify overlapping categories and weak classes.

